page.title: 01Freshfield to Woodvale
page.content: This diverse region in the county of {Merseyside}stretches from Freshfield in the South to Woodvale in the North, from the Western coastline inland to the moss-lands of the East. Bisecting this region is the Liverpool to Southport railway. Freshfield Station has been the focal point for the growth of this dormitory village. Also running through this region is the A565. This dual-carriageway is the major road from Liverpool to Southport and beyond. To the east of this road, cattle and sheep graze on the flat green fields. To the west of this road lies Woodvale Aerodrome. Woodvale is not only an RAF base, but is also the centre for recreational flying activities. Further west the Nature Reserve is home to many species, some endangered, of flora and fauna.
